		<div class="site-content" data-off-canvas-content>
<div class="grid-container grid-x">
	<div class="cell large-8 small-12 main-content-well">
		<div class="story-content">
							<div class="story-info">
			<div class="featured-img-container">
			<img class="story-img" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/now-departing-9781668062111_hr-1-726x400.jpeg" title="Brandon Taylor, Megha Majumdar, Susan Orlean, and more: 27 new books out today!">
					</div>
		<div class="story-heads">
		<h1>Brandon Taylor, Megha Majumdar, Susan Orlean, and more: 27 new books out today!</h1>
			</div>
	</div>
										<div class="byline-date">
					<span class="byline"><a href="https://lithub.com/author/juliahass/"  title="Julia Hass">Julia Hass</a></span>
					<span class="hr"></span>
					<span class="date">October 14, 2025</span>
				</div>
						<div class="story-body">
								<p style="text-align: left;">Literary fiction-heads (as LH devotees usually are) must celebrate: new Brandon Taylor AND Megha Majumdar in one week?! Not to mention exciting, unputdownable novels by Quan Barry, Anna North, Adam Johnson, and a selection of compelling and masterful stories by Thomas McGuane.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">If it&#8217;s nonfiction you seek, look no further. Susan Orlean has released a new memoir entitled <em>Joyride</em>, and a joy it is sure to be. Though there are also heavier options out there: a look at the generation who fought in World War II, and the wounds both visible and unseen they carried forever, a narrative encapsulation of the year the stock market fell, and a detailed history of the Spanish-American War.</p>
<p>Though there are many to choose from, I&#8217;ll be picking up Megha Majumdar, Gabrielle Hamilton, and Quan Barry this week. Happy reading!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">*</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="260667" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/?attachment_id=260667" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/minor-black-figures.jpg" data-orig-size="795,1200" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="minor black figures" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/minor-black-figures-199x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/minor-black-figures-678x1024.jpg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-260667" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/minor-black-figures-199x300.jpg" alt="" width="199" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/minor-black-figures-199x300.jpg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/minor-black-figures-678x1024.jpg 678w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/minor-black-figures-768x1159.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/minor-black-figures-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/minor-black-figures-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/minor-black-figures.jpg 795w" sizes="(max-width: 199px) 100vw, 199px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Brandon Taylor, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9780593332368" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Minor Black Figures</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(Riverhead)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;A story unafraid to foreground love and lust, and that treats emotional ambiguity as a starting point, not as the fuzzy ending common in literary fiction. A piercing, precise, and affecting tale of young love and high art.&#8221;<br />
<em>–Kirkus</em></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="256501" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2025-part-two/9780593804889-copy/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9780593804889-copy.jpg" data-orig-size="1333,2000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="Megha Majumdar, A Guardian and a Thief" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9780593804889-copy-200x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9780593804889-copy-682x1024.jpg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-256501" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9780593804889-copy-200x300.jpg" alt="Megha Majumdar, A Guardian and a Thief" width="200" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9780593804889-copy-200x300.jpg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9780593804889-copy-682x1024.jpg 682w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9780593804889-copy-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9780593804889-copy-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9780593804889-copy-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9780593804889-copy-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9780593804889-copy.jpg 1333w" sizes="(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Megha Majumdar, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9780593804872" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>A Guardian and a Thief</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(Knopf)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;Majumdar brilliantly blurs right and wrong, ethics and legality &#8230; [An] exquisitely wrenching novel.&#8221;<br />
<em>–Booklist</em></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="255955" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2025-part-two/71slicof9al-_ac_uf10001000_ql80_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/71sLiCOf9aL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" data-orig-size="676,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Susan Orlean, Joyride" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/71sLiCOf9aL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-203x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/71sLiCOf9aL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-255955" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/71sLiCOf9aL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-203x300.jpg" alt="Susan Orlean, Joyride" width="203" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/71sLiCOf9aL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-203x300.jpg 203w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/71sLiCOf9aL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-41x60.jpg 41w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/71sLiCOf9aL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-34x50.jpg 34w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/71sLiCOf9aL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg 676w" sizes="(max-width: 203px) 100vw, 203px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Susan Orlean, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9781982135164" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Joyride</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(Avid Reader Press)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;For anyone who’s asked—and haven’t we all—‘How does she write like that?,’ this wise and exuberant book is the answer. It’s funny, as well. Just masterful.”<br />
<em>–</em>David Sedaris</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="260626" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/quan-barry-on-writing-a-horror-novel-set-in-antarctica/unveiling_hc-no-author-photo/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/Unveiling_HC-No-Author-Photo-.jpeg" data-orig-size="1600,2423" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Unveiling_HC No Author Photo" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/Unveiling_HC-No-Author-Photo--198x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/Unveiling_HC-No-Author-Photo--676x1024.jpeg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-260626" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/Unveiling_HC-No-Author-Photo--198x300.jpeg" alt="" width="198" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/Unveiling_HC-No-Author-Photo--198x300.jpeg 198w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/Unveiling_HC-No-Author-Photo--676x1024.jpeg 676w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/Unveiling_HC-No-Author-Photo--768x1163.jpeg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/Unveiling_HC-No-Author-Photo--40x60.jpeg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/Unveiling_HC-No-Author-Photo--1014x1536.jpeg 1014w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/Unveiling_HC-No-Author-Photo--1352x2048.jpeg 1352w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/Unveiling_HC-No-Author-Photo--33x50.jpeg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/Unveiling_HC-No-Author-Photo-.jpeg 1600w" sizes="(max-width: 198px) 100vw, 198px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Quan Barry, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9780802165350" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>The Unveiling</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(Grove)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;A luxury trip to Antarctica goes horribly wrong in Barry&#8217;s triumph of literary horror &#8230; A terrifying must-read set at the ends of the Earth.&#8221;<br />
<em>–Kirkus</em></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="255918" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2025-part-two/attachment/9780399590092/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9780399590092.jpg" data-orig-size="298,450" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Gabrielle Hamilton, Next of Kin: A Memoir" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9780399590092-199x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9780399590092.jpg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-255918" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9780399590092-199x300.jpg" alt="Gabrielle Hamilton, Next of Kin: A Memoir" width="199" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9780399590092-199x300.jpg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9780399590092-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9780399590092-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9780399590092.jpg 298w" sizes="(max-width: 199px) 100vw, 199px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Gabrielle Hamilton, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9780399590092" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Next of Kin</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(Random House)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;In her singular, lyrical style, Hamilton has given us nothing less than an exploration of death, love, and the meaning of life.&#8221;<br />
<em>–</em>Ariel Levy</p>
<p><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="260963" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/brandon-taylor-megha-majumdar-susan-orlean-and-more-27-new-books-out-today/the-radical-fund-9781476765877_hr/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/the-radical-fund-9781476765877_hr.jpeg" data-orig-size="1400,2125" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="The Radical Fund, John witt" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/the-radical-fund-9781476765877_hr-198x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/the-radical-fund-9781476765877_hr-675x1024.jpeg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-260963 aligncenter" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/the-radical-fund-9781476765877_hr-198x300.jpeg" alt="The Radical Fund, John witt" width="198" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/the-radical-fund-9781476765877_hr-198x300.jpeg 198w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/the-radical-fund-9781476765877_hr-675x1024.jpeg 675w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/the-radical-fund-9781476765877_hr-768x1166.jpeg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/the-radical-fund-9781476765877_hr-40x60.jpeg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/the-radical-fund-9781476765877_hr-1012x1536.jpeg 1012w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/the-radical-fund-9781476765877_hr-1349x2048.jpeg 1349w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/the-ra