<p style="text-align: center;"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="260761" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/on-the-terrible-toll-of-the-last-bloody-year-of-wwii/the-wounded-generation-cover-art/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/THE-WOUNDED-GENERATION-cover-art.jpg" data-orig-size="619,941" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="THE WOUNDED GENERATION cover art" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/THE-WOUNDED-GENERATION-cover-art-197x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/THE-WOUNDED-GENERATION-cover-art.jpg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-260761" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/THE-WOUNDED-GENERATION-cover-art-197x300.jpg" alt="" width="197" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/THE-WOUNDED-GENERATION-cover-art-197x300.jpg 197w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/THE-WOUNDED-GENERATION-cover-art-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/THE-WOUNDED-GENERATION-cover-art-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/THE-WOUNDED-GENERATION-cover-art.jpg 619w" sizes="(max-width: 197px) 100vw, 197px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>David Nasaw, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9780593298695" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>The Wounded Generation: Coming Home After World War II</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(Penguin Press)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;Richly informative and compelling, <em>The Wounded Generation</em> is an important history of the tragedies of war and the triumphs of a democratic society that fully supports veterans&#8217; well-being.&#8221;<br />
<em>–Booklist</em></p>
<p><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="260962" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/brandon-taylor-megha-majumdar-susan-orlean-and-more-27-new-books-out-today/images-2-22/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/images-2.jpeg" data-orig-size="181,279" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Unfit, Ariana Harwicz" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/images-2.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/images-2.jpeg" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-260962 aligncenter" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/images-2.jpeg" alt="Unfit, Ariana Harwicz" width="181" height="279" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/images-2.jpeg 181w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/images-2-39x60.jpeg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/images-2-32x50.jpeg 32w" sizes="(max-width: 181px) 100vw, 181px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Ariana Harwicz, trans, by Jessie Mendez Sayer, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9780811238892" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Unfit</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(New Directions)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;Harwicz&#8217;s assured pacing is bolstered by her gorgeous and often darkly funny prose, immaculately translated by Mendez Sayer. The result is a wild and unforgettable ride.&#8221;<br />
<em>–Publishers Weekly</em></p>
<p><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="260821" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/who-was-peter-matthiessen-really/true-nature/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/true-nature.jpeg" data-orig-size="300,450" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="true nature" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/true-nature-200x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/true-nature.jpeg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-260821 aligncenter" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/true-nature-200x300.jpeg" alt="" width="200" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/true-nature-200x300.jpeg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/true-nature-40x60.jpeg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/true-nature-33x50.jpeg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/true-nature.jpeg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Lance Richardson, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9781524748319" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>True Nature: The Pilgrimage of Peter Matthiessen</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(Pantheon)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;Richardson’s fine-toothed research establishes Peter’s importance as a writer and a singular inhabitant of his time.&#8221;<br />
<em>–Alta</em></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="255948" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2025-part-two/a1xvfo509tl-_uf10001000_ql80_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/A1XVfo509tL._UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" data-orig-size="663,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Thomas McGuane, A Wooded Shore: And Other Stories" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/A1XVfo509tL._UF10001000_QL80_-199x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/A1XVfo509tL._UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-255948" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/A1XVfo509tL._UF10001000_QL80_-199x300.jpg" alt="Thomas McGuane, A Wooded Shore: And Other Stories" width="199" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/A1XVfo509tL._UF10001000_QL80_-199x300.jpg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/A1XVfo509tL._UF10001000_QL80_-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/A1XVfo509tL._UF10001000_QL80_-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/A1XVfo509tL._UF10001000_QL80_.jpg 663w" sizes="(max-width: 199px) 100vw, 199px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Thomas McGuane, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9780385350235" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>A Wooded Shore: And Other Stories</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(Knopf)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;Spare, engaging, and full of sardonic moments, McGuane&#8230;continues to show his mastery.&#8221;<br />
<em>–Booklist</em></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="260771" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/brandon-taylor-megha-majumdar-susan-orlean-and-more-27-new-books-out-today/71lpfcnut1l-_uf10001000_ql80_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/71LPFcNuT1L._UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" data-orig-size="663,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="1929, Andrew Ross Sorkin" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/71LPFcNuT1L._UF10001000_QL80_-199x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/71LPFcNuT1L._UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-260771" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/71LPFcNuT1L._UF10001000_QL80_-199x300.jpg" alt="1929, Andrew Ross Sorkin" width="199" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/71LPFcNuT1L._UF10001000_QL80_-199x300.jpg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/71LPFcNuT1L._UF10001000_QL80_-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/71LPFcNuT1L._UF10001000_QL80_-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/71LPFcNuT1L._UF10001000_QL80_.jpg 663w" sizes="(max-width: 199px) 100vw, 199px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Andrew Ross Sorkin, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9780593296967" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>1929: Inside the Greatest Crash in Wall Street History—and How It Shattered a Nation</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(Viking)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;This gripping account revisits timeless themes—greed, hubris, comeuppance—but it also sets that fateful year in a moment in time, at once distant, and bracingly familiar. A riveting, crucial read.&#8221;<br />
<em>–</em>Jill Lepore</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="255944" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2025-part-two/91dyum3a30l-_uf10001000_ql80_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/91dyUM3A30L._UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" data-orig-size="662,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Adam Johnson, The Wayfinder" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/91dyUM3A30L._UF10001000_QL80_-199x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/91dyUM3A30L._UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-255944" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/91dyUM3A30L._UF10001000_QL80_-199x300.jpg" alt="Adam Johnson, The Wayfinder" width="199" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/91dyUM3A30L._UF10001000_QL80_-199x300.jpg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/91dyUM3A30L._UF10001000_QL80_-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/91dyUM3A30L._UF10001000_QL80_-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/91dyUM3A30L._UF10001000_QL80_.jpg 662w" sizes="(max-width: 199px) 100vw, 199px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Adam Johnson, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9780374619572" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>The Wayfinder</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>MCD</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">“How lucky we are that Adam Johnson has ignited for us this wild, epic, and utterly captivating skein of human history.&#8221;<br />
<em>–</em>Jennifer Egan</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="260785" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/?attachment_id=260785" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/twice-born.jpg" data-orig-size="1400,2100" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="twice born" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/twice-born-200x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/twice-born-683x1024.jpg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-260785" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/twice-born-200x300.jpg" alt="" width="200" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/twice-born-200x300.jpg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/twice-born-683x1024.jpg 683w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/twice-born-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/twice-born-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/twice-born-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/twice-born-1365x2048.jpg 1365w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/twice-born-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/twice-born.jpg 1400w" sizes="(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Hester Kaplan, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9781646223091" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Twice Born: Finding My Father in the Margins of Biography</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(Catapult)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;Melancholy and meticulously written, this excavation of a literary lineage isn’t easy to forget.&#8221;<br />
<em>–Publishers Weekly</em></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="256108" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2025-part-two/9780593978207-copy/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9780593978207-copy.jpg" data-orig-size="662,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="Three or More Is a Riot: Notes on How We Got Here: 2012-Present" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9780593978207-copy-199x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9780593978207-copy.jpg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-256108" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9780593978207-copy-199x300.jpg" alt="Three or More Is a Riot: Notes on How We Got Here: 2012-Present" width="199" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9780593978207-copy-199x300.jpg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9780593978207-copy-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9780593978207-copy-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9780593978207-copy.jpg 662w" sizes="(max-width: 199px) 100vw, 199px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Jelani Cobb, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9780593978207" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Three or More is a Riot</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(One World)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;Insight, historical memory, reportage, pith, and, not least of all, wit. All these gifts he deploys here without missing a beat, effortlessly weaving them into his own distinctive style.&#8221;<br />
<em>–</em>Ta-Nehisi Coates</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="260772" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/brandon-taylor-megha-majumdar-susan-orlean-and-more-27-new-books-out-today/we-survived-the-night/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/we-survived-the-night.jpeg" data-orig-size="994,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="We Survived the Night, Julian Brave Noisecat" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/we-survived-the-night-199x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/we-survived-the-night-679x1024.jpeg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-260772" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/we-survived-the-night-199x300.jpeg" alt="We Survived the Night, Julian Brave Noisecat" width="199" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/we-survived-the-night-199x300.jpeg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/we-survived-the-night-679x1024.jpeg 679w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/we-survived-the-night-768x1159.jpeg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/we-survived-the-night-40x60.jpeg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/we-survived-the-night-33x50.jpeg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/we-survived-the-night.jpeg 994w" sizes="(max-width: 199px) 100vw, 199px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Julian Brave NoiseCat, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9780593320785" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>We Survived the Night</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(Knopf)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;Thoughtful, informative, often entertaining, and just as often saddening, [<em>We Survived the Night</em>] is a book to remember.&#8221;<br />
<em>–Kirkus</em></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="260713" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/poetry-for-everyone-remembering-courtney-kampa/brightandborrowedlight_hc/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/BrightandBorrowedLight_HC.jpg" data-orig-size="1678,2550" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="BrightandBorrowedLight_HC" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/BrightandBorrowedLight_HC-197x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/BrightandBorrowedLight_HC-674x1024.jpg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-260713" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/BrightandBorrowedLight_HC-197x300.jpg" alt="" width="197" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/BrightandBorrowedLight_HC-197x300.jpg 197w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/BrightandBorrowedLight_HC-674x1024.jpg 674w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/BrightandBorrowedLight_HC-768x1167.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/BrightandBorrowedLight_HC-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/BrightandBorrowedLight_HC-1011x1536.jpg 1011w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/BrightandBorrowedLight_HC-1348x2048.jpg 1348w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/BrightandBorrowedLight_HC-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/BrightandBorrowedLight_HC.jpg 1678w" sizes="(max-width: 197px) 100vw, 197px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Courtney Kampa, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9780063429451" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>A Bright and Borrowed Light: Poems</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(William Morrow)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;Courtney Kampa captures the wrecked and wondrous world with a brilliant command of deeply felt language and startling beauty &#8230; Kampa’s blazing, virtuosic syntax unspools like lush honey, drizzling over intensely ephemeral snapshots that flicker and blaze.&#8221;<br />
<em>–</em>Tiana Clark</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="255949" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2025-part-two/91flqa-8wel-_uf10001000_ql80_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/91flQA-8wEL._UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" data-orig-size="658,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Anna North, Bog Queen" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/91flQA-8wEL._UF10001000_QL80_-197x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/91flQA-8wEL._UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-255949" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/91flQA-8wEL._UF10001000_QL80_-197x300.jpg" alt="Anna North, Bog Queen" width="197" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/91flQA-8wEL._UF10001000_QL80_-197x300.jpg 197w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/91flQA-8wEL._UF10001000_QL80_-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/91flQA-8wEL._UF10001000_QL80_-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/91flQA-8wEL._UF10001000_QL80_.jpg 658w" sizes="(max-width: 197px) 100vw, 197px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Anna North, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9781635579666" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Bog Queen</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(Bloomsbury)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">“A remarkably crafted tale that asks important questions about the imprint we leave on our loved ones, our culture, and our land.”<br />
<em>–Booklist</em></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="260718" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/?attachment_id=260718" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/splendid-liberators-scaled.jpg" data-orig-size="1742,2560" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="splendid liberators" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/splendid-liberators-204x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/splendid-liberators-697x1024.jpg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-260718" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/splendid-liberators-204x300.jpg" alt="" width="204" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/splendid-liberators-204x300.jpg 204w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/splendid-liberators-697x1024.jpg 697w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/splendid-liberators-768x1129.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/splendid-liberators-41x60.jpg 41w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/splendid-liberators-1045x1536.jpg 1045w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/splendid-liberators-1393x2048.jpg 1393w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/splendid-liberators-34x50.jpg 34w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/splendid-liberators-scaled.jpg 1742w" sizes="(max-width: 204px) 100vw, 204px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Joe Jackson, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9780374191900" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Splendid Liberators: Heroism, Betrayal, Resistance, and the Birth of American Empire</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(FSG)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;Narrative nonfiction at its very best—intelligent, propulsive, and somehow both intimate and panoramic in scope. Americans should read it to understand how we became a world colonial power and how, in many senses, we lost our way.&#8221;<br />
<em>–</em>Hampton Sides</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="260794" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/brandon-taylor-megha-majumdar-susan-orlean-and-more-27-new-books-out-today/81j6u80wt9l-_uf10001000_ql80_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/81j6u80wt9L._UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" data-orig-size="658,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Workhorse, Caroline Palmer" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/81j6u80wt9L._UF10001000_QL80_-197x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/81j6u80wt9L._UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-260794" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/81j6u80wt9L._UF10001000_QL80_-197x300.jpg" alt="Workhorse, Caroline Palmer" width="197" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/81j6u80wt9L._UF10001000_QL80_-197x300.jpg 197w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/81j6u80wt9L._UF10001000_QL80_-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/81j6u80wt9L._UF10001000_QL80_-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/81j6u80wt9L._UF10001000_QL80_.jpg 658w" sizes="(max-width: 197px) 100vw, 197px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Caroline Palmer, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9781250360083" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Workhorse</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(Flatiron)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;Palmer renders Clo’s world in vivid, gritty detail alongside sharp commentary on class, ambition, and women’s roles in the publishing industry.&#8221;<br />
<em>–Booklist</em></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="255959" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2025-part-two/91cshde0njl-_ac_uf10001000_ql80_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/91CshDE0NJL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" data-orig-size="732,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Joe Sacco, The Once and Future Riot" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/91CshDE0NJL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-220x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/91CshDE0NJL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-255959" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/91CshDE0NJL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-220x300.jpg" alt="Joe Sacco, The Once and Future Riot" width="220" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/91CshDE0NJL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-220x300.jpg 220w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/91CshDE0NJL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-44x60.jpg 44w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/91CshDE0NJL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-37x50.jpg 37w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/91CshDE0NJL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg 732w" sizes="(max-width: 220px) 100vw, 220px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Joe Sacco, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9781250880260" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>The Once and Future Riot</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(Metropolitan)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;Meticulous and beautifully crafted &#8230; Paying homage to the importance of seeking truth, however elusive, this timely work is as powerful as it is artful.&#8221;<br />
<em>–Publishers Weekly</em></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="260798" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/brandon-taylor-megha-majumdar-susan-orlean-and-more-27-new-books-out-today/now-departing-9781668062111_hr/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/now-departing-9781668062111_hr.jpeg" data-orig-size="1400,2158" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Now Departing, Victor Sweeney" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/now-departing-9781668062111_hr-195x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/now-departing-9781668062111_hr-664x1024.jpeg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-260798" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/now-departing-9781668062111_hr-195x300.jpeg" alt="Now Departing, Victor Sweeney" width="195" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/now-departing-9781668062111_hr-195x300.jpeg 195w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/now-departing-9781668062111_hr-664x1024.jpeg 664w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/now-departing-9781668062111_hr-768x1184.jpeg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/now-departing-9781668062111_hr-39x60.jpeg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/now-departing-9781668062111_hr-996x1536.jpeg 996w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/now-departing-9781668062111_hr-1329x2048.jpeg 1329w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/now-departing-9781668062111_hr-32x50.jpeg 32w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/now-departing-9781668062111_hr.jpeg 1400w" sizes="(max-width: 195px) 100vw, 195px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Victor M. Sweeney, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9781668062111" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Now Departing: A Small-Town Mortician on Death, Life, and the Moments in Between</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(Gallery Books)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;This reflective book signifies the value of building relationships and is a highly recommended read.&#8221;<br />
<em>–Library Journal</em></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="260669" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/?attachment_id=260669" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/9781662603280.jpg" data-orig-size="800,1200" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="happy bad" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/9781662603280-200x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/9781662603280-683x1024.jpg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-260669" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/9781662603280-200x300.jpg" alt="happy bad" width="200" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/9781662603280-200x300.jpg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/9781662603280-683x1024.jpg 683w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/9781662603280-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/9781662603280-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/9781662603280-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/9781662603280.jpg 800w" sizes="(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Delaney Nolan, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9781662603280" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Happy Bad</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(Astra)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;Nolan leavens the novel with gallows humor &#8230; The darkness of this excellent novel is amplified by how terrifyingly plausible it all is.&#8221;<br />
<em>–Kirkus</em></p>
<p><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="260868" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/brandon-taylor-megha-majumdar-susan-orlean-and-more-27-new-books-out-today/attachment/9781250348227/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/9781250348227-scaled.jpeg" data-orig-size="1684,2560" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="The Zorg, Siddhartha Kara" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/9781250348227-197x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/9781250348227-674x1024.jpeg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-260868 aligncenter" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/9781250348227-197x300.jpeg" alt="The Zorg, Siddhartha Kara" width="197" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/9781250348227-197x300.jpeg 197w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/9781250348227-674x1024.jpeg 674w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/9781250348227-768x1167.jpeg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/9781250348227-39x60.jpeg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/9781250348227-1011x1536.jpeg 1011w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/9781250348227-1347x2048.jpeg 1347w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/9781250348227-33x50.jpeg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/9781250348227-scaled.jpeg 1684w" sizes="(max-width: 197px) 100vw, 197px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Siddharth Kara, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9781250348227" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>The Zorg: A Tale of Greed and Murder That Inspired the Abolition of Slavery</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(St. Martin&#8217;s Press)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;Enthralling and elegant &#8230; A harrowing glimpse of slavery’s horrors and an incisive investigation into one of history’s most reviled crimes.&#8221;<br />
<em>–Publishers Weekly</em></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="260799" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/brandon-taylor-megha-majumdar-susan-orlean-and-more-27-new-books-out-today/81dezvvgc1l-_uf10001000_ql80_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/81DeZvvGC1L._UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" data-orig-size="658,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="The Monsters We Make, Rachel Corbett" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/81DeZvvGC1L._UF10001000_QL80_-197x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/81DeZvvGC1L._UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-260799" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/81DeZvvGC1L._UF10001000_QL80_-197x300.jpg" alt="The Monsters We Make, Rachel Corbett" width="197" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/81DeZvvGC1L._UF10001000_QL80_-197x300.jpg 197w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/81DeZvvGC1L._UF10001000_QL80_-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/81DeZvvGC1L._UF10001000_QL80_-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/81DeZvvGC1L._UF10001000_QL80_.jpg 658w" sizes="(max-width: 197px) 100vw, 197px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Rachel Corbett, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9780393867695" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>The Monsters We Make: Murder, Obsession, and the Rise of Criminal Profiling</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(W. W. Norton)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;A highly readable, endlessly revealing primer on the homicidal mind.&#8221;<br />
<em>–Kirkus</em></p>
<p><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="260961" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/brandon-taylor-megha-majumdar-susan-orlean-and-more-27-new-books-out-today/attachment/9781250866783/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/9781250866783.jpeg" data-orig-size="1650,2550" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Future Boy, Michael J. Fox" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/9781250866783-194x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/9781250866783-663x1024.jpeg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-260961 aligncenter" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/9781250866783-194x300.jpeg" alt="Future Boy, Michael J. Fox" width="194" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/9781250866783-194x300.jpeg 194w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/9781250866783-663x1024.jpeg 663w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/9781250866783-768x1187.jpeg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/9781250866783-39x60.jpeg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/9781250866783-994x1536.jpeg 994w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/9781250866783-1325x2048.jpeg 1325w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/9781250866783-32x50.jpeg 32w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/9781250866783.jpeg 1650w" sizes="(max-width: 194px) 100vw, 194px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Michael J. Fox, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9781250866783" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Future Boy</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(Flatiron)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;The spirit of gratitude that runs through all of Mr. Fox’s books continues to be a pleasure and an attraction.&#8221;<br />
<em>–The Wall Street Journal</em></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="260440" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/cannibal-sororities-and-butterfly-girl-gangs-octobers-best-sci-fi-and-fantasy-books/happy-people-dont-live-here/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/happy-people-dont-live-here.jpg" data-orig-size="790,1200" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="happy people don&#8217;t live here" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/happy-people-dont-live-here-198x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/happy-people-dont-live-here-674x1024.jpg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-260440" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/happy-people-dont-live-here-198x300.jpg" alt="happy people don't live here" width="198" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/happy-people-dont-live-here-198x300.jpg 198w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/happy-people-dont-live-here-674x1024.jpg 674w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/happy-people-dont-live-here-768x1167.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/happy-people-dont-live-here-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/happy-people-dont-live-here-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/happy-people-dont-live-here.jpg 790w" sizes="(max-width: 198px) 100vw, 198px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Amber Sparks, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9781324094395" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Happy People Don&#8217;t Live Here</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(Liveright)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;This is an enthralling novel about how mothers haunt their daughters and vice versa, and the beautiful fact of love after death.&#8221;<br />
<em>–</em>Marie-Helene Bertino</p>
